This program generates and prints out the ascii character and hexadecimal codes for all characters from 0 to 7f (inclusive) using a loop. The `String.fromCharCode()` method is used to convert the decimal ASCII code to its corresponding character, and the `toString(16)` method is used to convert the decimal value to hexadecimal. The output shows all characters from space (`0x20`) to tilde (`0x7e`). Note that `0x0` to `0x9` are non-printable characters, so they are not included in the ASCII string.
